bras extends to the case where\nthe associated graded algebra is not necessarily commutative, but is finitely\ngenerated as a module over its center, which is the coordinate ring of a\nPoisson variety with finitely many symplectic leaves.\n  We also describe explicitly (in the settings of affine varieties and compact\nsmooth manifolds) the space of Poisson traces on X when X=V/G, where V is\nsymplectic and G is a finite group acting faithfully on V. In particular, we\nshow that this space is finite-dimensional.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Aug 2009 17:17:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Dec 2009 14:44:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 8 Jun 2010 21:10:59 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 22 Dec 2010 22:50:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-12-24"}
