ribution by nebulae reduces the mean energy of escaping LyC only\nby $\\approx10$% relative to that of stellar LyC. Therefore, the effect of the\nescape of nebular LyC on the reionization process may be small.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Aug 2009 01:38:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Sep 2009 02:03:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-14"}
